<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-03-10T12:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-03-10T12:00:00-05:00" n="920" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d920">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 855.48/479</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Minister in Belgium</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_WB1" type="to"><hi rend="italic">Whitlock</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-03-10T12:00:00-05:00">
                                    <hi rend="italic">March 10, 1917, noon</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>265. Your 46, March 3. Department feels that work must be maintained as
                            long as possible under American control and relinquished only when
                            Americans are forced out. Arrangements are being made to send force of
                            Dutchmen into Belgium to learn details of work under guidance of
                            American delegates. Take no steps looking to withdrawal pending receipt
                            of further instructions.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <persName corresp="#p_LR1">
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                                </persName>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>